text: Toybuk (, ), or Duwaybiq ( or ), also known as Duniq (), is a village in northern Aleppo Governorate, northwestern Syria. Located some north of the city of Aleppo, it administratively belongs to Nahiya Sawran in Azaz District. Nearby localities include Ihtaimlat to the west, Dabiq to the south, and Turkman Bareh to the southeast. In the 2004 census, Duwaybiq had a population of 1,862. ==References== Category:Turkmen communities in Syria
